    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-07-09T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-07-09T05:00:00-05:00" n="90"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10508: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-09T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 9, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 9—10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>552.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>The Chinese Minister for Foreign Affairs, C. T. Wang, is expected here tomorrow,
                    presumably to discuss the Manchurian situation with Chiang Kai-shek<note n="73"
                        xml:id="d90fn73">Chairman of the State Council of the National Government of
                        the Republic of China.</note> and Marshal Chang Hsüeh-liang.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
